Hello everyone! I use two libraries which are byteorder and trickster.

I'm working on a project I had done in C and now I have to convert it to rust.

I made a first test in my main and everything works:

```
fn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
  let ctx = Process::new("fakegame")?;
  println!("example process id: {}", ctx.get_pid());

  //let kind_of_remote_var: i32 = 1337;
  let x1: i64 = 0x7ffe76269df4;

  let mut read_byte_buffer = ctx.read_memory::<i64>(x1 as *const i64 as usize)?;


  println!("Read process memory is -> {}", read_byte_buffer.read_i32::<LittleEndian>()?);
  
  let mut write_buffer = Vec::new();
  write_buffer.write_i32::<LittleEndian>(10)?;
  ctx.write_memory::<i32>(x1 as *const i32 as usize, write_buffer)?;


  Ok(())
}
```
Now when I want to do separate functions I get an error message.
My code :


```
fn read_process_memory(processname: &str, address: i64) -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
    let mut x = Process::new(processname);

    let mut read_pm = x.read_memory::<i64>(address as *const i64 as usize);
    
    println!("Read process memory is -> {}", read_pm.read_i32::<LittleEndian>()?);
    
    Ok(())
}
```
And this is the error.
```
error[E0599]: no method named `read_memory` found for enum `std::result::Result<trickster::external::Process, anyhow::Error>` in the current scope
  --> src/main.rs:13:25
   |
13 |     let mut read_pm = x.read_memory::<i64>(address as *const i64 as usize);
   |                         ^^^^^^^^^^^ method not found in `std::result::Result<trickster::external::Process, anyhow::Error>`

error: aborting due to previous error
```

Can someone help me please.
Thanks
